To disable a specific rule you'll need the rule identifier which is displayed at the end of the lint error.

An error can be suppressed using `@Suppress` annotations:

```kotlin
// Suppressing all rules for the entire file
@file:Suppress("ktlint")

// Suppress a single rule (with id 'rule-id', defined in rule set with id 'rule-set-id') from the annotated construct
@Suppress("ktlint:rule-set-id:rule-id")
class Foo {}

// Suppress multiple rules for the annotated construct
@Suppress("ktlint:standard:no-wildcard-imports", "ktlint:custom-rule-set-id:custom-rule-id")
import foo.*

// Suppress all rules for the annotated construct
@Suppress("ktlint")
import foo.*
```

!!! warning "Deprecated: ktlint-disable and ktlint-enable directives"
    The `ktlint-disable` and `ktlint-enable` directives in EOL and block comments are deprecated and will be removed in a future version. The experimental rule `ktlint-suppression` can be used to automatically replace these directives with `@Suppress` annotations. Enable this rule with `.editorconfig` property `ktlint_standard_ktlint-suppression = enabled`."}

